1.text: Park the vehicles so the batteries are near each other.

2.text: Engage the parking brake on both cars.

3.text: Turn the cars off and remove the keys.

4.text: Check the batteries to make sure they are the same voltage.

5.text: Locate the positive and negative battery terminals in each car.

6.text: Separate the jumper cable clamps by laying them on the ground.

7.text: Clamp a red clamp to the positive terminal of the dead battery.

8.text: Secure the other red clamp to the positive terminal on the donor battery.

9.text: Connect a black clamp to the negative terminal on the donor battery.

10.text: Clamp the other black lead to an unpainted metal surface in the car.

11.text: Start the donor vehicle and let it idle for a few minutes.

12.text: Turn on the dead car’s engine.

13.text: Disconnect the jumper cables in reverse, starting with the black clamps.
